				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The main point of CrashTest's routine is that it's about 2x faster than the fastest controller read routine we had before, not that it doesn't use a byte of memory during reading; not using a byte simply means it's faster. I've tried it in the DMC-fortified read and it halves the time to around 370 clocks. It's quite an improvement, and could even be a few clocks faster if it assumed a value for the upper 6 bits.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

